Description: Medium sized axe head made of basalt in a trapezoidal shape, tapered towards the butt end. The blade end is convex, the butt end is rounded. Well smoothed surface. Extensive traces of use at the blade end with bigger parts chipped off. The section is straight, slightly tapered towards the blade end.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.10, Filling of east door of level III
